### Testes da API de Autenticação
### Use este arquivo no REST Client (VS Code Extension) ou Postman

### Variáveis
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5340
@token = seu-token-aqui

###############################################
### 1. CADASTRO DE USUÁRIO
###############################################
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "João Silva",
  "email": "joao@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

# Resposta esperada:
# {
#   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
#   "user": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "name": "João Silva",
#     "email": "joao@email.com"
#   }
# }

###############################################
### 2. LOGIN
###############################################
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "joao@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

# Resposta esperada:
# {
#   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
#   "user": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "name": "João Silva",
#     "email": "joao@email.com"
#   }
# }

###############################################
### 3. BUSCAR USUÁRIO ATUAL
###############################################
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# Resposta esperada:
# {
#   "id": 1,
#   "name": "João Silva",
#   "email": "joao@email.com"
# }

###############################################
### 4. LISTAR TASKS DO USUÁRIO
###############################################
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# Resposta esperada:
# [
#   {
#     "id": 1,
#     "title": "Minha tarefa",
#     "isCompleted": false,
#     "category": 0,
#     "priority": 1,
#     "order": 0,
#     "userId": 1,
#     "createdAt": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z"
#   }
# ]

###############################################
### 5. CRIAR NOVA TASK
###############################################
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Nova tarefa do usuário",
  "isCompleted": false,
  "category": 0,
  "priority": 1,
  "order": 0
}

# Nota: UserId será automaticamente preenchido pelo backend

###############################################
### 6. ATUALIZAR TASK
###############################################
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Tarefa atualizada",
  "isCompleted": true,
  "category": 0,
  "priority": 2,
  "order": 0
}

# Só funciona se a task pertencer ao usuário autenticado

###############################################
### 7. DELETAR TASK
###############################################
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# Só funciona se a task pertencer ao usuário autenticado

###############################################
### TESTE DE SEGURANÇA
###############################################

### Tentar acessar tasks sem token (deve falhar)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks

# Resposta esperada: 401 Unauthorized

### Tentar cadastrar com email duplicado (deve falhar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Outro Usuário",
  "email": "joao@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

# Resposta esperada: 400 Bad Request
# { "message": "Email já cadastrado" }

### Login com senha errada (deve falhar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "joao@email.com",
  "password": "senha-errada"
}

# Resposta esperada: 401 Unauthorized
# { "message": "Email ou senha inválidos" }

###############################################
### FLUXO COMPLETO DE TESTE
###############################################

### 1. Cadastrar Usuário 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Usuário 1",
  "email": "user1@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 2. Criar task para Usuário 1 (copie o token da resposta anterior)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer COLE-O-TOKEN-AQUI
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Task do Usuário 1",
  "isCompleted": false,
  "category": 0,
  "priority": 1,
  "order": 0
}

### 3. Cadastrar Usuário 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Usuário 2",
  "email": "user2@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 4. Listar tasks do Usuário 2 (deve estar vazio)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer COLE-O-TOKEN-DO-USER2-AQUI

### 5. Criar task para Usuário 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer COLE-O-TOKEN-DO-USER2-AQUI
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Task do Usuário 2",
  "isCompleted": false,
  "category": 0,
  "priority": 1,
  "order": 0
}

### 6. Verificar que Usuário 1 só vê suas tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN-DO-USER1

### 7. Verificar que Usuário 2 só vê suas tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN-DO-USER2

###############################################
### COMO USAR ESTE ARQUIVO
###############################################

# Opção 1: REST Client (VS Code Extension)
# 1. Instale a extensão "REST Client" no VS Code
# 2. Abra este arquivo
# 3. Clique em "Send Request" acima de cada requisição

# Opção 2: Postman
# 1. Importe este arquivo no Postman
# 2. Execute cada requisição manualmente
# 3. Copie e cole os tokens quando necessário

# Opção 3: cURL (terminal)
# Cadastro:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:5340/api/auth/register \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"name":"João Silva","email":"joao@email.com","password":"123456"}'

# Login:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:5340/api/auth/login \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"email":"joao@email.com","password":"123456"}'

# Listar tasks (substitua TOKEN):
# curl -X GET http://localhost:5340/api/tasks \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
